Tales of the Legion #349
Publisher: DC Comics
Publication Date: July 1987

Writer: Paul Levitz
Pencillers: Greg LaRocque; Norm Breyfogle
Inkers: Larry Mahlstedt; Mike DeCarlo and Arne Starr
Colorists: Carl Gafford
Letterer: John Costanza
Cover: Curt Swan, Dan Bulandi, and Anthony Tollin

Some members of the Legion of Super-Heroes express their suspicion when it comes to the real identity of their recent teammate, Sensor Girl. Meanwhile, Wildfire, Polar Boy and Colossal Boy go to the Legion Academy to investigate the disappearance of their recent student, Mentalla, who has simply left without a word. Meanwhile, Emerald Empress continues to find individuals to join the ranks of her new Fatal Five. She has searched for the whereabouts of Validus, but her searches have proven fruitless. Meanwhile, a professional thief named Flare battles some Science Police officers to steal a prized spacecraft and succeeds. The theft gains the attention of the Emerald Empress and she recruits Flare for the new Fatal Five. Meanwhile, Element Lad, as leader of the Legion of Super-Heroes, questions Sensor Girl about her identity because it is causing too much turmoil within the Legion. Sensor Girl decides to quit the Legion to prevent any further tribulation.

